<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="889" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d889">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/487.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 4, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Clark requests me to say: “Receivers unanimously demand immediate
                            settlement location and deny my right to locate them. Have taken stand
                            on inclosures Department’s No. 27, May 15. Each Receiver seeking to be
                            sustained by his Government. Shall insist on exercise of right to
                            designate location. Vital principle involved. Serious disagreement
                            imminent.”</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bundy.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>